All 6 tests pass. Here's what was done:

**Bug:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

The loop condition `i < items.length - 1` caused the loop to stop one element short (visiting indices `0..N-2` instead of `0..N-1`), so the last item was always skipped.

**Fix:** Removed `- 1` from the condition:
```typescript
// Before (broken)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

All 6 tests now pass ✓

